	"dateModified": "2020-06-12T18:12:27.000Z",
	"keywords": "Flutter, Mobile App Development",
	"description": "In this post we&#x27;ll take a look at the provider pattern in Flutter. Some other\npatterns, such as BLoC Architecture, use the provider pattern internally. But\nthe provider pattern is far easier to learn and has much less boilerplate code.\n\nIn this post, we’ll take the default Counter app provided by Flutter and\nrefactor it to use the provider pattern.\n\nIf you want to know what the Flutter team at Google has to say about the\nprovider pattern, check out this 2019 talk\n[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v",
	"headline": "How to Use the Provider Pattern in Flutter",
	"author": {
		"@type": "Person",
		"name": "Ayusch Jain",
